42. Quae tenet, quae videatur. Observe the two relative clauses, one in the indicative, the other in the subjunctive mood. In the first the antecedent ‘ ea' is regarded as a simple demonstrative pronoun‚ in the second as=talis, and therefore requiring a subjunctive. The sense of the passage would admit of both clauses being treated either way: the shade of difference expressed by the combination of the two is an instance of the flexible power of the relative in Latin,
